
[1]geld

   GELD, n. Money; tribute; compensation. This word is obsolete in
   English,but it occurs in old laws and law books in composition; as in
   Danegeld, or Danegelt, a tax imposed by the Danes; Weregeld,
   compensation for the life of a man, &c.

   GELD. v.t. pret. gelded or gelt; pp. gelded or gelt.

   1. To castrate; to emasculate.

   2. To deprive of any essential part.

   3. To deprive of any thing immodest or exceptionable.
